<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 01 at 4:55PM EST  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Floyd,
northwestern Polk and southwestern Bartow Counties through 530 PM
EST...
At 454 PM EST, a strong thunderstorm was over Cedartown, moving
northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, and enhanced tornado
risk.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rome, Cedartown, Euharlee, Taylorsville, Seney, Lindale and
Stilesboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
